OL,6,FThe row reared its head in public for
OL,7,Fthe first time last Thursday, when
OL,8,FLowe gave an interview to the Daily
OL,9,FMail criticising Farage and casting
OL,10,Fdoubt on whether he could be prime
OL,11,Fminister one day.
OL,13,FLowe said it was "too early to know
OL,14,Fwhether Nigel will deliver the goods",
OL,15,Fdescribing Reform as a "protest party
OL,16,Fled by the Messiah".
OL,18,FFarage then responded in an interview
OL,19,Fon Talk TV, dismissing the comments as
OL,20,F"utterly, completely wrong".
